{"word":"H4454 - מָלַק - mâlaq - maw-lak' - Wring off","slug":"H4454","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">מָלַק</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>mâlaq"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>maw-lak'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Wring off"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05DE;&#x05DC;&#x05E7; - ma&#x0302;laq</b> - <i>maw-lak'</i><p/>A primitive root; to <i>crack</i> a joint; by implication to <i>wring</i> the neck of a fowl (without separating it): - wring off."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H4462\">H4462</a>, <a href=\"#/H4471\">H4471</a>, <a href=\"#/H4478\">H4478</a>, <a href=\"#/H4482\">H4482</a>"}]}